---
description: Frontend rules for React ecommerce UI
alwaysApply: false
---

## Tech Stack
- React (Vite)
- JavaScript (or TypeScript optional)
- Tailwind CSS
- Axios

## Structure
- pages/
- components/
- api/
- context/

## Component Rules
- Use functional components
- Use React hooks (useState, useEffect)
- Keep components small and reusable

## UI/UX
- Modern ecommerce design (Nike/Adidas style)
- Responsive (mobile-first)
- Clean layout with spacing and shadows
- Use grid system for products

## State Management
- Use Context API (or Redux Toolkit)
- Global state for cart and auth

## API Integration
- Use axios instance
- Handle:
  - loading state
  - error state

## Features
- Product list with filters
- Product detail page
- Cart system
- Login/Register
- Wishlist

## Code Quality
- Avoid inline logic in JSX
- Separate logic and UI
- Reuse components
